HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1471
By Sparks
A RESOLUTION to commend Andrea Medina for exemplary
service as an intern for the University of
Tennessee Division of Government Relations,
Advocacy, and Economic Development.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this General Assembly is pleased to recognize
certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment
of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Andrea Medina is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her
role as an intern for the University of Tennessee Division of Government Relations, Advocacy,
and Economic Development; Ms. Medina's work has resulted in numerous benefits for the
University of Tennessee System and the campus community as a whole; and
WHEREAS, a native of Smyrna, Ms. Medina is a student at the University of Tennessee,
Knoxville, where she is pursuing a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science and is set to
graduate in May 2026, having earned a commendable 3.63 grade point average and consistent
recognition on the Dean's List; and
WHEREAS, throughout her academic career, Andrea Medina has demonstrated strong
leadership and a commitment to service, including her role as a resident assistant in Hess Hall,
in which position she supports the safety, well-being, and engagement of fellow students; and
WHEREAS, eager to expand her knowledge and gain practical experience in
government and public policy, Ms. Medina brought her talents to Capitol Hill during the 2026
session of the One Hundred Fourteenth General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout her internship, Andrea Medina has surpassed all expectations,
demonstrating professionalism, intellectual curiosity, and a strong work ethic in service to the
State of Tennessee; and
HJR1471
018018
- 1 -

WHEREAS, a proud member of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Inc., Ms. Medina
exemplifies a commitment to scholarship, leadership, and service both on campus and in the
broader community; and
WHEREAS, her prior experience as a research analyst intern and undergraduate
researcher reflects her analytical abilities and dedication to understanding complex policy and
political environments; and
WHEREAS, Andrea Medina has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight
and rare decorum, earning the respect and admiration of her colleagues and supervisors; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Andrea Medina for outstanding service as an intern
for the University of Tennessee Division of Government Relations, Advocacy, and Economic
Development and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
